docs.abstract: Congressional Memo; retired United States Senators Trent Lott, Tom Daschle and John B Breaux are combining to push an expansion of tele-medicine as a way to improve national health care access and cut costs; say the idea of using the nation’s growing digital capacity to provide more health care has significant bipartisan support and could be solution to the partisan schism over the Affordable Care Act.

docs.lead_paragraph: The board of Nevada’s troubled insurance exchange voted to cut ties with Xerox and instead rely on the federal enrollment system.

headline.main: Health Site Under Fire, Nevada Alters Path
headline.print_headline: Health Site Under Fire, Nevada Alters Path

docs.abstract: Board governing Nevada's problem-plagued online health insurance exchange votes unanimously to sever ties with Xerox, vendor that had a $72 million contract to build the Nevada exchange and has been paid $12 million to date; exchange has been riddled with problems, including billing and enrollment errors that led to class-action lawsuit; board members vote to rely on federal enrollment system for at least a year.
